---

## API Design Overview

This project is a RESTful API built for the University of Westminster Smart Campus initiative.
The API manages physical **Rooms** and the **Sensors** deployed within them, along with a
full historical log of **Sensor Readings**. It is implemented using JAX-RS with Jersey 2.39.1
running on Apache Tomcat 9.

### Resource Hierarchy

```
/api/v1
├── /                               ← Discovery endpoint (HATEOAS metadata)
├── /rooms                          ← Room collection (GET all / POST create)
│   └── /{roomId}                   ← Individual room (GET / DELETE)
└── /sensors                        ← Sensor collection (GET all / POST create)
    └── /{sensorId}                 ← Individual sensor (GET)
        └── /readings               ← Sub-resource: reading history (GET / POST)
```

### Core Data Models

The API is built on three POJO entities:

| Entity | Key Fields |
|--------|-----------|
| **Room** | id, name, capacity, sensorIds (List) |
| **Sensor** | id, type, status (ACTIVE / MAINTENANCE / OFFLINE), currentValue, roomId |
| **SensorReading** | id (UUID), timestamp (epoch ms), value |

### In-Memory Data Storage

All data is stored using `ConcurrentHashMap` (thread-safe) inside a singleton `DataStore`
class. No database is used, as required by the coursework specification.

### Design Principles Applied

- Proper HTTP status codes (200, 201, 400, 403, 404, 409, 422, 500)
- JSON-only request and response bodies via `@Produces` / `@Consumes(APPLICATION_JSON)`
- Resource nesting via the JAX-RS Sub-Resource Locator pattern (Part 4)
- Centralised error handling via custom Exception Mappers (Part 5)
- Cross-cutting logging via JAX-RS ContainerRequestFilter / ContainerResponseFilter (Part 5)
- HATEOAS links provided in the Discovery endpoint (Part 1)

