## Sample curl Commands

### 1. Discovery Endpoint — GET /api/v1
```bash
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1
```
**Expected:** 200 OK — API metadata and HATEOAS resource links

---

### 2. Get All Rooms — GET /api/v1/rooms
```bash
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/rooms
```
**Expected:** 200 OK — full list of all room objects including LIB-301 and LAB-101

---

### 3. Create a New Room — POST /api/v1/rooms
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/rooms ^
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" ^
  -d "{\"id\":\"ENG-205\",\"name\":\"Engineering Design Studio\",\"capacity\":40}"
```
**Expected:** 201 Created — the new room object is returned

---

### 4. Get a Specific Room — GET /api/v1/rooms/{roomId}
```bash
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/rooms/LIB-301
```
**Expected:** 200 OK — full details of room LIB-301

---

### 5. Delete a Room That Has No Sensors — DELETE /api/v1/rooms/{roomId}
```bash
curl -X DELETE http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/rooms/ENG-205
```
**Expected:** 200 OK — room successfully deleted (only works if no sensors are assigned)

---

### 6. Try to Delete a Room That Has Sensors — Error Test (409)
```bash
curl -X DELETE http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/rooms/LIB-301
```
**Expected:** 409 Conflict — room still has sensors assigned, deletion blocked

---

### 7. Get All Sensors — GET /api/v1/sensors
```bash
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/sensors
```
**Expected:** 200 OK — full list of all sensors

---

### 8. Filter Sensors by Type — GET /api/v1/sensors?type=CO2
```bash
curl -X GET "http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/sensors?type=CO2"
```
**Expected:** 200 OK — only CO2 sensors returned

---

### 9. Create a New Sensor — POST /api/v1/sensors
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/sensors ^
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" ^
  -d "{\"id\":\"OCC-001\",\"type\":\"Occupancy\",\"status\":\"ACTIVE\",\"currentValue\":0,\"roomId\":\"LIB-301\"}"
```
**Expected:** 201 Created — sensor is created and linked to room LIB-301

---

### 10. Create Sensor with Invalid roomId — Error Test (422)
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/sensors ^
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" ^
  -d "{\"id\":\"FAKE-999\",\"type\":\"Gas\",\"status\":\"ACTIVE\",\"currentValue\":0,\"roomId\":\"GHOST-ROOM\"}"
```
**Expected:** 422 Unprocessable Entity — roomId GHOST-ROOM does not exist

---

### 11. Post a Sensor Reading — POST /api/v1/sensors/{sensorId}/readings
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/sensors/TEMP-001/readings ^
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" ^
  -d "{\"value\":24.7}"
```
**Expected:** 201 Created — new reading saved with auto UUID and timestamp.
Side effect: TEMP-001 `currentValue` is updated to 24.7 automatically.

---

### 12. Get Sensor Reading History — GET /api/v1/sensors/{sensorId}/readings
```bash
curl -X GET http://localhost:8080/SmartCampusAPI/api/v1/sensors/TEMP-001/readings
```
**Expected:** 200 OK — full list of all historical readings for TEMP-001

